HEADWORD: Thalia
<hw>Tha*li"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>Qa`leia</grk>, originally, blooming, luxuriant, akin to
<grk>qa`llein</grk> to be luxuriant.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>That one of the nine Muses who presided over
comedy.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the three Graces.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>One of the Nereids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thaliacea</ent>⟦br⟧
